cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

The paper deals with real-time object detection and tracking, which is a core problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a new learning framework that embeds distribution-related constraints into the multi-channel correlation filters (MCCF), which is a machine learning technique. Hence, it can also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of intelligent production for industrial 4.0 applications, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed method is also applicable to robotics, which is a subfield of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper mentions the use of a new dataset, which can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
